briefdescription.para: Handle ROS parameters and perform the necessary updated in the hardware.
Add the list of adis parameters to m_attr_current_device.
Add the list of IIO update functions to m_func_map_update_int32_params map. This map contains the update APIs for each int32 type parameter.
Add the list of IIO read functions to m_func_map_get_int32_params map. This map contains the read APIs for each int32 type parameter.
Add the list of IIO update functions to m_func_map_update_uint32_params map. This map contains the update APIs for each uint32 type parameter.
Add the list of IIO read functions to m_func_map_get_uint32_params map. This map contains the read APIs for each uint32 type parameter.
Add the list of IIO update functions to m_func_map_update_double_params map. This map contains the update APIs for each double type parameter.
Add the list of IIO read functions to m_func_map_get_double_params map. This map contains the read APIs for each double type parameter.
Add the list of IIO command functions to m_func_map_execute_commands map. This map contains the command APIs for which can be triggered in the hardware.
Add a parameter description for each parameter in m_param_description.
Declare the ros parameters and initialize their values with values read from hardware.
Update all ros parameter values by reading them from hardware.
Handles a parameter change of type double. Performs the necessary updates in the hardware and logs the result.
Handles a parameter change of type int32. Performs the necessary updates in the hardware and logs the result.
Handles a parameter change of type uint32. Performs the necessary updates in the hardware and logs the result.
Handles a command. Trigger the command in the hardware if necessary and logs the result.
